title: ‘Most tolled city in the world’: Sydney to introduce two-way tolling on Harbour Bridge
description: Sky News host Steve Price discusses Sydney becoming the “most tolled” city in the world as Premier Chris Minns is set to introduce two-way tolling.  “Sydney now has the dubious title, announced today, of being the most tolled city in the world,” Mr Price said.   “New South Wales Premier Chris Minns announced he was introducing two-way tolling on the iconic Sydney Harbour Bridge and Harbour Tunnel in 2028.”

title: ‘Cost of fanaticism’: Green energy transition is an ‘ideological push’ to make people poorer
description: Reform UK Councillor Darren Grimes says the green energy transition is “the cost of fanaticism”.  Mr Grimes told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio that it is an “ideological push” by the UK government.  “To make the poor, poorer and colder.”

title: World’s Gone Mad: Lefties in meltdown over Pantone’s ‘Color of the Year’ decision
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean calls out the “hysterical woke women” protesting Pantone’s 'Color of the Year' decision.

title: ‘Ominous sign’: UK going ‘broke and backwards’ in its renewable race
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio says UK Labour’s green energy plan is an “ominous sign” for Australia.  Ms De Giorgio said the UK’s green energy plan could cost £350 billion.  “Looks like the UK is going broke and backwards as well in its race to renewables.”

title: MP expense scandal labelled ‘dangerous’ as questions on government reform grow
description: Former speaker of the house Bronwyn Bishop discusses the ongoing Labor MP expense scandal as questions are raised over government reform.   “I just look at it with the greatest of cynicism,” Ms Bishop told Sky News host Rowan Dean.   “It’s dangerous, because there are too many people with not enough to do, all of who think they should be ministers.”

title: ‘Deep flaws’ with Melbourne’s new West Gate Tunnel
description: Transport Planning Consultant William McDougall says Melbourne’s new West Gate Tunnel has “deep flaws” in the traffic forecasting and the economic appraisal.

title: Suburban Rail Loop 24-hour construction site ‘affecting local residents’
description: Sky News host Steve Price says the 24-hour Suburban Rail Loop construction site noise and vibration is “affecting local residents”.

title: ‘It’s a joke’: Victoria’s Indigenous Treaty reverses progress of Australia
description: Indigenous Leader Warren Mundine says Victoria’s Indigenous Treaty is “a joke” as Premier Jacinta Allan apologises to Indigenous Victorians.

title: ‘Widespread anger’ in UK as Afghan asylum seekers jailed for rape of 15-year-old girl
description: Sky News contributor Adrian Hayes reacts to reports of two Afghan asylum seekers raping a 15-year-old girl.   “There is widespread anger, of course, because it is not just an isolated incident,” Mr Hayes told Sky News host Steve Price.   “It’s happening all too regularly.”

title: ‘Obscene joke’: Australia’s government perks are encouraging ‘greedy politicians’
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean says Canberra is full of “greedy politicians” using taxpayer money for their personal benefits.  Mr Dean said taxpayers are spending money on “freebies” for the government.  “If these vast sums of money and unbelievable entitlements are within the guidelines, then the guidelines are a sick and obscene joke, a rort even.”

title: Donald Trump continues his ‘scathing’ attacks on Somalia
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean says US President Donald Trump has continued his “scathing” attacks on Somalia.  Mr Dean said the fraud scandal “deepens” in the state of Minnesota.  “The administration is cracking down on immigration and targeting the state's large Somali community.”

title: Children are incredibly resourceful and will ‘get around’ social media ban
description: One Nation MP Barnaby Joyce says children are incredibly resourceful and will “get around” the social media ban.

title: Donald Trump has ‘no filter’ when it comes to things ‘on his mind’
description: Political Commentator Stephanie Hamill says US President Donald Trump has “no filter” on things he does.  Ms Hamill told Sky News host Rowan Dean that Donald Trump “says what’s on his mind”.  “And as a voter, I honestly support people speaking their mind versus them saying something and doing something different.”

title: Minnesota accused of one of the biggest ‘welfare fraud schemes’ in US history
description: Political Commentator Stephanie Hamill says Minnesota is accused of participating in one of the biggest “welfare fraud schemes” in US history.  Ms Hamill told Sky News host Rowan Dean that the situation is “totally absurd”.  “And this is something that has really frustrated Americans for so many years.”

title: Donald Trump ‘trolling big time’ with his fast-track US citizenship card
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean says US President Donald Trump has launched an “extraordinary” Trump Gold Card to fast-track US citizenship.  Mr Dean said the cost of the card is $1 million.  “Well, that’s trolling big time.”
